txt.en: Although the Dwarves of Gabilshathûr are no longer trapped beyond the Rammas Deluon, its miners face new challenges as the creatures of Angmar reclaim the fallen realm.\n\nYour mission is to aid the Dwarves of Gabilshathûr in repelling an infestation of blade-beaks.
Although the Dwarves of Gabilshathûr are no longer trapped beyond the Rammas Deluon, its miners face new challenges as the creatures of Angmar reclaim the fallen realm.
You have completed your mission.\n\nYou should talk to Vorthur Smokebreath at Akrâz-zahar.

'I have a new mission for you, [placeholder].

'I have received an urgent message from the dwarves at Gabilshathûr. It seems that even though they are no longer troubled by Orcs and the Men of Angmar, the blade-beaks that have long dwelled in the region have grown a bit more numerous and much more dangerous than they anticipated! Burrows have been cropping up in the centre of Gabilshathûr for several days now, and if they are not soon sealed, it is feared the blade-beaks will overrun the settlement.

'You are to travel to Gabilshathûr and aid the dwarves there in sealing these burrows!'
You may be ambushed after completing your objective.
Your mission is to aid the Dwarves of Gabilshathûr in repelling an infestation of blade-beaks.\n\nYou should talk to Vorthur Smokebreath and travel to Gabilshathûr.
'Well done, [placeholder]!\n\n'I suppose if it is not one thing, it's another. Angmar is not the most hospitable land, even for the hardiest of dwarves!'
